<paragraph blockId="5.[556,1108,659,1073]" lastBlockId="5.[140,1108,1082,1671]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">
These represent the first verifiable records of this species in North America (see below) (
<figureCitation box="[1026,1090,976,1002]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[140,174,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[139,1108,903,1603]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[140,1108,903,1601]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Distribution of Ilyobates bennetti, Meotica exilis, Meotica “pallens,” Lathrobium fulvipenne, and Oxytelus sculptus in eastern Canada." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3773938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3773938/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). The specimens collected in Point Pleasant Park were found in scolytine galleries under the bark of a dead white pine (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[804,947,1082,1108]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="strobus">
<emphasis box="[804,947,1082,1108]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Pinus strobus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sprengel ex F.Rudolphi" authorityYear="1830" box="[993,1096,1082,1109]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Pinaceae</taxonomicName>
). Co-inhabiting 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[314,439,1117,1143]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
included 
<taxonomicName authority="(Say, 1834)" baseAuthorityName="Say" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[562,915,1117,1143]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Nudobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cephalus">
<emphasis box="[562,770,1117,1143]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Nudobius cephalus</emphasis>
(Say, 1834)
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille, 1803-" authorityYear="1802" box="[935,1095,1117,1144]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Staphylinidae</taxonomicName>
); and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kirby, 1837)" baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[191,601,1152,1178]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Polygraphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufipennis">
<emphasis box="[191,436,1152,1178]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Polygraphus rufipennis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kirby WF" box="[453,593,1152,1178]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" refId="ref10004" refString="Kirby WF (1837) Th e insects. In: Richardson J (Ed) Fauna boreali-Americana or the Zoology of the northern parts of British America, containing descriptions of the objects of natural history collected on the late northern land expeditions, under the command of Captain Sir John Franklin, Fletcher, RN. Norwich, xxxix + 325 pp." type="book" year="1837">Kirby, 1837</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="LeConte, 1876" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1876" box="[662,1108,1152,1178]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pityophthorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cariniceps">
<emphasis box="[662,925,1152,1178]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Pityophthorus cariniceps</emphasis>
LeConte, 1876
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[148,315,1187,1213]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Curculionidae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1804" box="[324,446,1187,1214]" class="Insecta" family="Scolytinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Scolytinae</taxonomicName>
). Th e specimen at Frenchman’s Cave was collected in a wet, mossy area in a gypsum sinkhole.
</paragraph>
